The presidency on Wednesday confirmed the release of the abducted Dapchi girls. According to a statement by the Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, who confirmed this to newsmen in Abuja the girls are being transported to safety. “Yes, the girls are being transported to safety. We will give details later. We thank God,” he said. Our reporter has confirmed that 5 out of the 106 abducted girls may have died while in the custody of Boko Haram. The abducted schoolgirls were returned in nine vehicles.  Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook